<p style="font-size: 21px;"><strong>Itinerary</strong></p>
<p><strong>Day 1:</strong><br />Transfer by coach from the airport to Stresa and stay 4 nights at the Hotel Astoria in Stresa.</p>
<p><strong>Days 2-4:</strong><br />Relax and enjoy 3 full days to explore the elegant town of Stresa and stunning <a data-udi="umb://document/476c8caf3fe84faab565f2d0f2e99f48" href="/{localLink:umb://document/476c8caf3fe84faab565f2d0f2e99f48}" title="Lake Maggiore">Lake Maggiore</a>. You might like to visit the Borromean Islands or the botanical Gardens of Villa Taranto which were once frequented by Ernest Hemingway. You can go on the Mottarone cable-car which now meets a chairlift to the summit with beautiful views as far as the Po Valley.</p>
<p><strong>Day 5:</strong><br />Take a direct transfer to Cadenabbia on Lake Como and stay 7 nights at the Grand Hotel Cadenabbia.</p>
<p><strong>Day 6:</strong><br />Bergamo Excursion - Enjoy a guided visit to one of <a data-udi="umb://document/a1a80922d88a43f8ba80b182c72e8904" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a1a80922d88a43f8ba80b182c72e8904}" title="Italy">Italy's</a> most impressive medieval cities. The cost of the ferry ticket to the pick up point in Varenna is not included (approx. €8 return). Excursion includes guided visit of some of Bergamo's most notable monuments and churches in the afternoon as well as free time to wander the cobbled streets and enjoy the local specialities - both savoury and sweet. </p>
<p><strong>Days 7-9: </strong><br />Relax and enjoy a few days in <a data-udi="umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a}" title="Lake Como">Lake Como</a> and drink in its dramatic scenery. You might like to take a ferry over to lovely Bellagio or visit the famous Villa Carlotta, situated a short walk away. Alternatively, Como town is easily reached by local bus or ferry where you can enjoy the cafe culture of the provincial capital. The small town of Varenna is beautiful and boasts some lovely lake front restaurants - well worth the short ferry ride. </p>
<p><strong>Day 10:</strong><br />St Moritz and the Bernina Express Excursion - travel to <a data-udi="umb://document/92803bd348ec48c1b64d53e77931172d" href="/{localLink:umb://document/92803bd348ec48c1b64d53e77931172d}" title="Switzerland">Switzerland</a> for a memorable day to glitzy St Moritz and a ride on the wonderful Bernina Express train from Poschiavo. Our most popular excursion on Lake Como, this full day outing includes time in Tirano where you might like to visit its remarkable cathedral as well as a stop on the way home in the quaint town of Chiavenna - perfect for an ice cream or coffee in the cobbled piazza. </p>
<p><strong>Day 11:</strong><br />A final day to take in some sunshine and enjoy the beautiful lake. </p>
<p><strong>Day 12:</strong><br />Transfer to the airport for your flight home.</p>
<p> </p>
<p style="font-size: 21px;"><strong>Departure dates &amp; prices for 2019</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Saturday departures, returning Wednesdays only for 11 nights</li>
<li>Prices from £1529 per person based on 4 star accommodation</li>
<li>Single rooms available with a supplement</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p style="font-size: 21px;"><strong>What’s included</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Return flights to Milan from the UK on Saturdays,</li>
<li>Transfers by coach between the airport and your hotels</li>
<li>Direct transfer from Lake Maggiore to Lake Como</li>
<li>11 nights half board accommodation in 4 star hotels</li>
<li>2 excursions: Full day St. Moritz and the Bernina Express &amp; half day in Bergamo</li>
<li>Assistance of Inghams Reps while in resort</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p style="font-size: 21px;"><strong>Your Hotels</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Stresa <a data-udi="umb://document/8f2c75297bbc4cfd97537af8e21f423d" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8f2c75297bbc4cfd97537af8e21f423d}" title="Astoria Hotel"> Hotel Astoria</a> ★★★★ (4 nights)</li>
<li>Cadenabbia <a data-udi="umb://document/db2b21b0e989403093f91c70f5f98cd4" href="/{localLink:umb://document/db2b21b0e989403093f91c70f5f98cd4}" title="Grand Hotel Cadenabbia">Grand Hotel Cadenabbia</a> ★★★★ (7 nights)</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p style="font-size: 21px;"><strong>Departure flights to Milan from:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Gatwick, Heathrow, Stansted, Luton</li>
<li>Birmingham, Manchester, Edinburgh &amp; Bristol</li>
<li>Flight supplements may apply</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
